# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from your Supabase project settings: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Discord Configuration
# Get your server ID: Right-click your server → Copy Server ID (enable Developer Mode in Discord settings)
# Get role IDs: Server Settings → Roles → Right-click premium roles → Copy Role ID
DISCORD_GUILD_ID=your-discord-server-id
DISCORD_PREMIUM_ROLE_IDS=role-id-1,role-id-2,role-id-3

# ================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ================================
#
# 1. Create a Supabase project at https://supabase.com/dashboard
#
# 2. Enable Discord OAuth in Supabase:
#    - Go to Authentication → Providers → Discord
#    - Create Discord app at https://discord.com/developers/applications
#    - Copy Client ID and Client Secret to Supabase
#    - Add redirect URL: https://your-project.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#
# 3. Configure Discord App:
#    - OAuth2 → Add redirect: https://your-project.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#    - Bot → Enable "Server Members Intent" (if using bot for role checks)
#    - OAuth2 → Scopes: identify, guilds.members.read
#
# 4. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values
#
# 5. For Vercel deployment, add these same variables in Vercel dashboard
